<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1913,2013]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This species is separated from other 
<taxonomicName box="[556,727,1986,2013]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ferenta species</taxonomicName>
by its wider, more ovuloid orange hindwing band. It has a more southern distribution than other 
<taxonomicName box="[511,599,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ferenta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ferenta</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[659,707,151,177]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality is 
<collectingCountry box="[830,898,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and all specimens and images we have seen are from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[360,431,187,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, with records extending as far south as 
<collectingRegion box="[876,1090,187,213]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
. There are recent photographs, but we are not aware of recent specimens and no COI 5’ sequences were available.
</paragraph>
